news.title: Hyderabad: Realtors join fray to buy Rajiv Swagruha flats
news.para: Official sources said there has been an overwhelming response to the auction. About 14,000 people have applied to purchase 3,000 flats and the number of applications might touch 30,000 in the next 20 days.

news.title: Rajasthan housing board to complete building MLA flats by August
news.para: The eight-storied towers have been constructed and the officials claimed that a 6-lakh sq feet roof has been cast in record time of five months.

news.title: RWAs in Hyderabad come up with new initiative to increase greenery
news.para: The RWAs said that as the city is losing its green cover due to several infrastructure projects, they have decided to increase greenery inside the residential complexes apart from public places.

news.title: MCZMA gets legal notice over delay in approving redevelopment plans in Mumbai
news.para: In its notice, the Association has said the proposals have been pending for approval for a considerable period of time since the constitution of the new committee in December last year.

news.title: Mahira Homes buyers protest at Haryana RERA office
news.para: In a letter to H-Rera chairman KK Khandelwal, the homebuyers said that the action plan should be shared with the homebuyers by Friday.

news.title: Mumbai-based Suraj Estate Developers gets Sebi nod for IPO
news.para: The proceeds from its fresh issuance worth Rs 315 crore for the repayment or prepayment of borrowings, in full or part of all or certain borrowings for the company and its subsidiary.

news.title: The Ramco Cements' profit down 45% at Rs 118 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Total revenue was up 4.94 per cent at Rs 1,722.68 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 1,641.53 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal.

news.title: PE inflows in real estate down 62% at $1.18 billion in Jan-March quarter
news.para: As per the data, PE investments in office segment fell to USD 732 million during January-March period from USD 2,148 million in the year-ago period, while the inflows in residential segment fell to USD 73 million from USD 234 million.

news.title: Oberoi Realty inks joint development pact for 18.3-acre land in Thane
news.para: The company has formed a revenue-share alliance with the landowner, who will receive 23% of net realisations as part of deal compensation. The developer has also paid Rs 50 crore to the land owner as an upfront adjustable and refundable deposit while executing the agreement.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body ramps up drive against C&D waste
news.para: If any agency (government or private) or any individual household is found piling up C&D waste on roadside or any other public place, the BMC is penalising individuals and government agencies.

news.title: Guwahati civic body tells shopping malls not to charge parking fees
news.para: GMC commissioner Devasish Sharma said, “We have received complaints from the public against the shopping malls and business establishments over the practice of collecting parking fees violating the GMC’s previous order."

news.title: Blox acquires realty advisory firm Plinthstone for $1.5 million
news.para: "Plinthstone's team that is servicing these projects will now be integrated into Blox," the company said in a statement. Blox did not disclose the deal value. However, the market sources said that it is around USD 1.5 million.

news.title: Non-payment of TDS not a ground for initiation of insolvency process: NCLAT
news.para: The NCLT had directed to initiate insolvency proceedings against Team Taurus Realty & Infrastructure over non-payment of two TDS amounts of Rs 66,884 and Rs 1.10 lakh.

news.title: SILA acquires Forbes Facility Services from Shapoorji Pallonji Group
news.para: With this acquisition, SILA's facilities management services business will strengthen its presence in North India and widen its service offerings, to include catering.

news.title: Rajasthan: Registration for phase-II of AIS Residency from May 26
news.para: In this multi-storey housing scheme, only officers of All India Services, Central Civil Services Group-A Services, Central Armed Police Forces, ARAs, RPS and RACS officers can apply.
